with one dollar of the money...

782
00:40:09,201 --> 00:40:11,291
that he so carefully earned.

783
00:40:11,995 --> 00:40:17,415
Therefore you have to answer Morris's
four questions of financial worthiness.

784
00:40:17,459 --> 00:40:18,589
Are you ready?

785
00:40:19,711 --> 00:40:21,091
I think so. Yes.

786
00:40:22,673 --> 00:40:24,303
Question number one:

787
00:40:25,050 --> 00:40:27,340
Where did you go to high school?

788
00:40:27,386 --> 00:40:29,046
Plainfield Public High.

789
00:40:29,096 --> 00:40:33,346
Question number two:
Who were you in high school?

790
00:40:34,101 --> 00:40:35,561
I was valedictorian.

791
00:40:36,687 --> 00:40:39,187
The smartest student in the school.

792
00:40:39,231 --> 00:40:40,521
That's good, right?

793
00:40:41,441 --> 00:40:42,611
Perhaps.

794
00:40:43,193 --> 00:40:48,913
Joy might be a brilliant,
unrealized creator of commerce.

795
00:40:49,366 --> 00:40:50,486
But on the other hand...

796
00:40:50,534 --> 00:40:54,504
it's equally possible that she is
a fatally flawed underachiever...

797
00:40:54,538 --> 00:40:59,668
doomed to a lifetime of failure,
disappointment, unfulfilled expectations.

798
00:41:00,752 --> 00:41:02,462
You must admit, Joy...

799
00:41:02,504 --> 00:41:05,554
that your life, to date,
makes a stronger case for...

800
00:41:06,550 --> 00:41:07,880
disappointment.

801
00:41:10,095 --> 00:41:11,635
I don't care about any of this.

802
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:14,560
It's not only risky,
but it's fiscally irresponsible...

803
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:17,060
and doesn't make any sense, whatsoever.

804
00:41:17,102 --> 00:41:18,602
Joy's never run a business in her life.

805
00:41:18,645 --> 00:41:20,965
I've been running my father's garage
for the last 10 years.

806
00:41:21,648 --> 00:41:23,228
Our father.

807
00:41:24,443 --> 00:41:26,953
I have ventures that I'm planning
to launch here...

808
00:41:26,987 --> 00:41:29,027
at this existing business.

809
00:41:29,072 --> 00:41:31,532
You never mentioned any of this...

810
00:41:31,575 --> 00:41:33,745
until I came to Trudy
to ask for an investment.

811
00:41:34,578 --> 00:41:37,038
What's Morris's third question?

812
00:41:37,080 --> 00:41:38,540
Are you prepared...

813
00:41:38,582 --> 00:41:42,092
within six months of commencing
this venture...

814
00:41:42,127 --> 00:41:44,127
to show adequate returns?

815
00:41:44,963 --> 00:41:46,723
I accept your terms.

816
00:41:46,757 --> 00:41:48,217
Don't do it, Joy.

817
00:41:48,258 --> 00:41:50,258
What's the fourth question?

818
00:41:50,302 --> 00:41:54,812
You are in a room,
and there is a gun on the table.

819
00:41:54,848 --> 00:41:59,558
And the only other person in the room
is an adversary in commerce.

820
00:41:59,603 --> 00:42:01,983
Only one of you can prevail.

821
00:42:02,022 --> 00:42:07,782
Yet, you have protected your business
and Morris's money.

822
00:42:09,738 --> 00:42:11,948
Do you pick up the gun, Joy?

823
00:42:13,534 --> 00:42:15,794
That's a very strange question.

824
00:42:15,827 --> 00:42:19,827
There is nothing strange
about this question at all.

825
00:42:19,873 --> 00:42:21,793
This is money.

826
00:42:23,001 --> 00:42:26,801
Do you pick up the gun?

827
00:42:27,756 --> 00:42:29,336
I pick up the gun.

828
00:42:29,383 --> 00:42:30,513
Good.

829
00:42:31,426 --> 00:42:33,886
I'm going to remember that you said that...

830
00:42:34,888 --> 00:42:37,348
when I speak to my lawyer.

831
00:42:38,392 --> 00:42:40,772
What did Trudy's lawyer say?

832
00:42:40,811 --> 00:42:42,901
He did a worldwide patent search.

833
00:42:42,938 --> 00:42:44,358
What's a patent?

834
00:42:45,274 --> 00:42:48,744
A patent is like a law
that you get to protect your idea.

835
00:42:49,111 --> 00:42:51,361
A lot of people patent their ideas...

836
00:42:51,405 --> 00:42:54,075
but only a few of them
actually get their ideas made.

837
00:42:54,908 --> 00:42:56,948
So Trudy just wanted to be careful...

838
00:42:56,994 --> 00:42:58,374
Joy...

839
00:42:58,412 --> 00:43:02,372
I just wanted to let you know that
Touissant has almost finished his work.

840
00:43:02,416 --> 00:43:03,746
And, um...

841
00:43:05,169 --> 00:43:07,629
You know, we really need to find
some more work for him.

842
00:43:07,671 --> 00:43:09,961
- You want more work in the house?
- Yeah.

843
00:43:10,007 --> 00:43:11,797
I have another big job I have to go to.

844
00:43:12,676 --> 00:43:14,296
- What?
- Yes.

845
00:43:14,344 --> 00:43:16,474
- Well, but we have real issues here.
- Sorry.

846
00:43:16,972 --> 00:43:18,972
- We don't have money for that work, Mom.
- Well...

847
00:43:19,683 --> 00:43:20,683
Okay.

848
00:43:21,935 --> 00:43:23,435
Joy...

849
00:43:23,937 --> 00:43:25,357
What is happening to you, Mother?

850
00:43:25,397 --> 00:43:27,187
I don't know what's going on.

851
00:43:27,232 --> 00:43:28,862
Are you in love with Touissant?

852
00:43:30,027 --> 00:43:32,357
I was feeling alone.

853
00:43:33,822 --> 00:43:37,032
And I didn't even realize it,
you know?

854
00:43:37,075 --> 00:43:38,235
And then...

855
00:43:43,707 --> 00:43:45,877
What did the patent search find?

856
00:43:47,127 --> 00:43:49,207
Trudy just wanted to be careful.

857
00:43:49,671 --> 00:43:52,221
And this guy found a man that's in Texas...

858
00:43:52,257 --> 00:43:55,007
who worked for another guy
in another country...

859
00:43:55,052 --> 00:44:00,022
where they have an idea
that might be similar to my mop.

860
00:44:00,057 --> 00:44:01,307
What country?

861
00:44:01,808 --> 00:44:02,848
Hong Kong.

862
00:44:02,893 --> 00:44:06,693
The Hong Kong man
has a representative in Dallas, Texas.

863
00:44:06,730 --> 00:44:10,400
The Dallas man was very reasonable
with my lawyer.

864
00:44:11,693 --> 00:44:12,743
Hey.

865
00:44:19,743 --> 00:44:21,373
So, this guy in Texas...

866
00:44:22,246 --> 00:44:26,076
We're supposed to pay him a royalty
on the patent as a protection, right?

867
00:44:26,333 --> 00:44:27,043
Right.

868
00:44:27,084 --> 00:44:28,714
To be safe from any claims.

869
00:44:28,752 --> 00:44:29,922
Is that correct?

870
00:44:29,962 --> 00:44:32,052
Please stop using the word "we."

871
00:44:32,089 --> 00:44:34,549
None of this is your money
or your business.

872
00:44:34,591 --> 00:44:38,431
But the same guy
also owns a manufacturing plant...

873
00:44:38,470 --> 00:44:41,560
that you guys say that it's cheaper
than any other place?

874
00:44:41,598 --> 00:44:43,308
- Yes. In California.
- Yes.

875
00:44:43,350 --> 00:44:45,890
A metal and plastic injection mold factory.

876
00:44:45,936 --> 00:44:47,056
Okay, so it's the same guy.

877
00:44:47,104 --> 00:44:48,864
- He owns the patent...
- This happens all the time in business.

878
00:44:48,897 --> 00:44:51,267
You find the best partner. It's smart.

879
00:44:51,316 --> 00:44:53,686
He doesn't understand business.
He doesn't know business.

880
00:44:53,735 --> 00:44:56,105
- No, no, I'm the first to say that.
- I understand business.

881
00:44:56,154 --> 00:44:59,574
Dad and I, we buy parts for the trucks
all the time at the garage.

882
00:44:59,616 --> 00:45:01,406
Morris did it all the time.

883
00:45:01,451 --> 00:45:03,871
One-stop shopping. It's the cheapest.

884
00:45:03,912 --> 00:45:05,332
- But is that normal?
- That's how he made his money.

885
00:45:05,372 --> 00:45:06,542
- Yeah, that's normal.
- Yes!

886
00:45:06,582 --> 00:45:08,382
But is it normal, the same guy
who has the patent...

887
00:45:08,417 --> 00:45:10,097
is the same guy who has the manufacturing?

888
00:45:10,127 --> 00:45:11,457
- Yeah. Make it best.
- Yeah.

889
00:45:11,503 --> 00:45:13,423
- Yeah?
- Better if it's that way.

890
00:45:13,463 --> 00:45:15,593
Okay, and the lawyer?
Right? Morris's lawyer?

